EU debate: countdown to the referendum – Guardian Live event

2016-06-21

As the final week of campaigning heats up, the Guardian’s political editor 




Chaired by 




It has been more than 40 years since the UK electorate was last able to decide whether the UK should be part of the European Union. After four months of intensive campaigning, unlikely cross-party collaborations and international interventions, now it is time to decide: is the UK better off in or out?

